UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 80
1 AN ACT relating to health care billing practices.
2 Be it enacted by the General Assembly of the Commonwealth of Kentucky:
3 Section 1. KRS 216B.250 is repealed, reenacted as a new section of KRS
4 Chapter 367, and amended to read as follows:
5 (1) For purposes of this section:[,]
6 (a) "Claim status" means one (1) of the following:
7 1. One (1) or more claims have been filed for the service or supply by the
8 facility or provider with a third-party payor;
9 2. One (1) or more claims are anticipated to be filed for the service or
10 supply by the facility or provider with a third-party payor; or
11 3. A claim will not be filed for the service or supply by the facility or
12 provider with any third-party payor;
13 (b) "Federal No Surprises Act" means Division BB of the Consolidated
14 Appropriations Act, 2021, Pub L. No. 116-260, as amended, and any federal
15 guidance or regulations issued thereunder;
16 (c) "Health care services":
17 1. Means the provision of health care services and any related supplies to
18 a patient by a health facility or any other provider of health care; and
19 2. Includes the provision of:
20 a. Prescription drugs, as defined in KRS 315.010; and
21 b. Home medical equipment, as defined in KRS 309.402;
22 (d) "Health facility":
23 1. Has the same meaning as in KRS 216B.015; and
24 2. Includes a medical laboratory;
25 (e) "In-network provider" means a health facility or any other provider of
26 health care that has a contractual relationship with the third-party payor to
27 provide health care services to the patient;
Page 1 of 13
XXXX 12/19/2025 1:59 PM Jacketed

UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 80
1 (f) "Medical laboratory" has the same meaning as in KRS 333.020;
2 (g) "Price classification" means one (1) of the following:
3 1. The facility's or provider's list price;
4 2. A price that has been contracted with a third-party payor; or
5 3. A price that is less than the facility's or provider's list price but has not
6 been contracted with a third-party payor;
7 (h) "Provider of health care":
8 1. Means a provider of hospital, medical, surgical, dental, vision, or
9 audiology services and any related supplies; and
10 2. Includes a provider of nursing, mental health, substance abuse,
11 chiropractic, pharmaceutical, podiatric, habilitative or rehabilitative
12 therapy, medical laboratory, medical imaging, radiation therapy, and
13 ambulance services and any related supplies; and
14 (i) "Total payment" means the sum of the following:
15 1. Any payments from a third-party payor;
16 2. Any out-of-pocket payments, including copayments, coinsurance, and
17 deductibles, that are required under the terms and conditions of
18 coverage or reimbursement provided by a third-party payor; and
19 3. Any other payments["Paying patient" means persons receiving health
20 care services who pay directly for services rendered, patients with
21 private health insurance or health maintenance organization coverage,
22 persons receiving Medicaid or Medicaid benefits under Title XVIII and
23 Title XIX of the Social Security Act and persons receiving veteran's
24 health care benefits. "Paying patient" does not include medically
25 indigent persons with no source of payment whatsoever].
26 (2) (a) [When a copy of an itemized statement is requested by any paying patient,
27 ]Each health facility or other provider of health care shall:
Page 2 of 13
XXXX 12/19/2025 1:59 PM Jacketed

UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 80
1 1. When a statement of charges or bill is requested by a patient, or
2 patient's authorized representative, for health care services that have
3 been provided to the patient, furnish to the patient or representative
4 within thirty (30) days of the patient's discharge or within fifteen (15)
5 days of the[ patient's] request, whichever is later, a[one (1) copy free of
6 charge of the itemized] statement of the health care services provided to
7 the patient; and[rendered and charges incurred by the patient]
8 2. When the facility or provider requests payment from any patient, or
9 patient's authorized representative, for health care services, furnish to
10 the patient or representative a statement of the health care services for
11 which payment is requested.
12 (b) A statement required under paragraph (a) of this subsection shall:
13 1. Include an itemization of each service and supply for which payment
14 is, or is anticipated to be, requested;
15 2. For each itemized service or supply:
16 a. Provide a plain language explanation of the service or supply;
17 b. Include sufficient detail to identify the specific service or supply
18 that was, or is anticipated to be, provided to the patient;
19 c. Indicate:
20 i. The date the service or supply was, or is anticipated to be,
21 provided;
22 ii. The total payment that is, or is anticipated to be, requested
23 by the facility or provider for the service or supply;
24 iii. The price classification for the amount identified under
25 subpart ii. of this subdivision; and
26 iv. The claim status;
27 d. If a claim for the service or supply has been, or is anticipated to
