1 be, filed by the facility or provider with any third-party payor,
2 indicate for each claim or anticipated claim:
3 i. The name of the third-party payor;
4 ii. For filed claims, a claim number or other claim identifier
5 utilized by the third-party payor for the claim;
6 iii. Whether the facility or provider is an in-network provider;
7 iv. Whether an assignment of benefits has been obtained; and
8 v. The amount the facility or provider has been, or is
9 anticipated to be, paid by the third-party payor for the
10 service or supply;
11 e. If any payments have been made to the facility or provider for
12 the service or supply, indicate:
13 i. The name of each payor;
14 ii. The amount of each payment; and
15 iii. The date of each payment; and
16 f. If, on the date the statement is furnished, any payment for the
17 service or supply is requested by the facility or provider directly
18 from the patient or patient's authorized representative, indicate:
19 i. The due date of the payment; and
20 ii. The amount of the requested payment;[A summary
21 statement of services rendered and charges incurred by the
22 patient shall be included with the invoice sent by a health
23 facility to the patient. Each invoice shall indicate that an
24 itemized statement may be obtained upon request. The
25 Cabinet for Human Resources shall impose a civil fine of
26 five hundred dollars ($500) for each violation by a health
27 care facility for failure to provide an itemized statement as
