1 required under this section.]
2 3. Not refer to a billing code, drug code number, or other assigned
3 numerical code without including the name of the health care service
4 that corresponds with the code;
5 4. Comply with subsection (6) of this section;
6 5. Conspicuously display:
7 a. The name and location of the facility or provider; and
8 b. A telephone number and electronic mail address of one (1) or
9 more appropriate staff of the facility or provider that can, and
10 are authorized to, answer questions and resolve disputes about
11 the statement; and
12 6.(c) The itemized statement shall ]Be stamped "Kentucky Revised Statutes
13 prohibit the use of this statement for insurance payment purposes where
14 benefits have been assigned."
15 (c) All of the information required under paragraph (b) of this subsection shall
16 be furnished to the patient, or patient's authorized representative, in a:
17 1. Single consolidated statement; and
18 2. Clear and coherent manner using language and format that is easily
19 readable and understandable by an ordinary layperson.
20 (d) A health facility or any other provider of health care shall:
21 1. Not bill or otherwise charge a patient, or patient's authorized
22 representative, for the preparation of a statement required under this
23 subsection; and
24 2. Comply with a request by a patient, or patient's authorized
25 representative, to furnish a statement required under this subsection to
26 the patient or representative by any of the following means:
27 a. By hand delivery or otherwise allowing the patient or
