1 the total price charged[charges] as reported in a[an itemized] statement furnished
2 under subsection (2) of this section and that which is reported to a third-party[third
3 party] payor, or at any time that a[ health] facility or provider becomes aware of
4 such a discrepancy, the[ health] facility or provider shall provide the patient, or if
5 applicable, the patient's authorized representative, and the third-party[third party]
6 payor with notification, an explanation, and, if applicable, any reconciliation of the
7 discrepancy in total charges.
8 (6) (a) A health facility or any other provider of health care shall not request or
9 accept a total payment for health care services that exceeds any of the
10 following amounts:
11 1. The price the facility or provider has agreed to receive for the health
12 care services under a contract entered with a third-party payor; or
13 2. The amount the facility or provider is entitled to receive for the health
14 care services under state or federal law.
15 (b) To aid in the effectuation of this subsection, the Attorney General may
16 enforce any state or federal law, including the federal No Surprises Act,
17 that regulates the maximum amount that a health facility or any other
18 provider of health care is entitled to bill or receive for health care services.
19 (7) A health facility or any other provider of health care that makes a good-faith
20 error resulting in a violation of this section may cure the violation if the facility
21 or provider, within thirty (30) days of the date of the violation:
22 (a) Remedies the violation by taking the action that was required under this
23 section;
24 (b) Notifies the patient, patient's authorized representative, and third-party
25 payor, as applicable, of the compliance failure; and
26 (c) Makes all appropriate refunds, adjustments, and corrections, as applicable.
27 (8) (a) Unless otherwise cured in accordance with subsection (7) of this section, a
