1 violation of this section shall be deemed to be an unfair, false, misleading,
2 or deceptive act or practice in the conduct of trade or commerce in violation
3 of KRS 367.170.
4 (b) All of the remedies, powers, and duties provided to the Attorney General or
5 any other person under KRS 367.110 to 367.300, and the penalties provided
6 in KRS 367.990, pertaining to acts and practices declared unlawful by KRS
7 367.170, shall apply with equal force and effect to a violation of this section.
8 (9) (a) Unless otherwise cured in accordance with subsection (7) of this section:
9 1. The Attorney General may institute an action in any court of
10 competent jurisdiction against any health facility or other provider of
11 health care alleged to have violated this section; and
12 2. A person injured by a violation of this section may institute an action
13 in any court of competent jurisdiction against any health facility or
14 other provider of health care alleged to have committed the violation.
15 (b) In any action brought under this subsection, if the court finds that the
16 health facility or other provider of health care has violated this section:
17 1. The plaintiff may:
18 a. Obtain an injunction to enjoin a continuance of the unlawful
19 activity;
20 b. Recover actual damages sustained, which shall be paid to the
21 injured person or persons; and
22 c. Be awarded reasonable attorney's fees and costs; and
23 2. In addition to the remedies and penalties provided under
24 subparagraph 1. of this paragraph:
25 a. The Attorney General may recover a civil penalty of not more
26 than five hundred dollars ($500) per violation; and
27 b. Any other plaintiff may recover a statutory penalty of not more
