8 Section 6. KRS 216B.300 is amended to read as follows:
9 As used in KRS 216B.300 to 216B.320 and KRS 216B.990(4)[(5)], unless the context
10 requires otherwise:
11 (1) "Cabinet" means the Cabinet for Health and Family Services or its designee.
12 "Designee" means any agency established under KRS Chapter 211 or KRS
13 147A.050 whose duties related to this chapter shall be set forth in administrative
14 regulation;
15 (2) "Secretary" means the secretary of the Cabinet for Health and Family Services;
16 (3) "Boarder" means a person who does not require supervision or assistance related to
17 medication, activities of daily living, or a supervised plan of care; and
18 (4) "Boarding home" means any home, facility, institution, lodging, or other
19 establishment, however named, which accommodates three (3) or more adults not
20 related by blood or marriage to the owner, operator, or manager, and which offers
21 or holds itself out to offer room and board on a twenty-four (24) hour basis for hire
22 or compensation. It shall not include any facility which is otherwise licensed and
23 regulated by the cabinet or any hotel as defined in KRS 219.011(3).
24 Section 7. This Act takes effect January 1, 2027.
